-- OTP Bank Hires Former FHB Bank CEO Gyuris for New Division, Mortgage Unit
-- B y   B a l a z s   P e n z
-- 2010-10-25T15:10:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/otp-bank-hires-former-fhb-bank-ceo-gyuris-for-new-division-mortgage-unit.html
OTP Bank Nyrt., Hungary’s largest
lender, hired  Daniel Gyuris , the former chief executive officer
of local mortgage lender  FHB  Bank Nyrt., as a deputy deputy CEO
in charge of a new division for real estate, agricultural and
small enterprise financing.  Gyuris will also take over as the chairman and CEO of OTP’s
mortgage-lending unit and its building society, the Budapest-
based lender said in a statement posted on the website of the
Budapest Stock Exchange today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Balazs Penz  at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  